1
00:00:10,275 --> 00:00:11,819
- [Emcee] Ladies and gentlemen,

2
00:00:11,819 --> 00:00:15,574
receiving his fourth decoration
for meritorious service,

3
00:00:15,574 --> 00:00:17,995
Lieutenant Ray Harlan.

4
00:00:17,995 --> 00:00:21,165
(audience applauding)

5
00:00:28,676 --> 00:00:30,053
- [Dispatcher] All
units in the vicinity

6
00:00:30,053 --> 00:00:32,848
of central Manhattan
bus terminal respond

7
00:00:32,848 --> 00:00:35,102
to a possible hostage situation.

8
00:00:35,102 --> 00:00:36,729
Shots have been fired.

9
00:00:39,190 --> 00:00:40,317
(gunshots banging)

10
00:00:40,317 --> 00:00:41,694
- [Ray] No!

11
00:00:41,694 --> 00:00:44,407
- [Mom] Oh god, my boy!

12
00:00:44,407 --> 00:00:45,992
- [Doctor] It's the
opinion of this doctor

13
00:00:45,992 --> 00:00:48,078
that due to his involvements
in recent events culminating

14
00:00:48,078 --> 00:00:51,166
in the death of an 11-year-old
boy, it would be best

15
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:54,128
if Lieutenant Harlan be
relieved of duty until...

16
00:01:04,309 --> 00:01:08,023
- [Vlad] My people and I
make millions each year

17
00:01:08,023 --> 00:01:11,360
while you scrape by
on the cop's salary.

18
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,195
Justice, hm.

19
00:01:23,294 --> 00:01:24,629
- [Lou] Ray, will you come home?

20
00:01:24,629 --> 00:01:27,007
There are other
cops in New York.

21
00:01:27,007 --> 00:01:29,219
You don't have to be there.

22
00:01:29,219 --> 00:01:31,055
You need some family.

23
00:01:31,055 --> 00:01:33,058
Besides, I need you now.

24
00:01:45,117 --> 00:01:47,202
- [Darcy] Ray Harlan,
ladies and gentlemen,

25
00:01:47,202 --> 00:01:50,707
whose accomplishments
include four service awards,

26
00:01:50,707 --> 00:01:54,838
three years with the NYPD, and
one very distinguished honor,

27
00:01:54,838 --> 00:01:57,759
jumping the bones of
Mary-Jo Bronkowski.

28
00:02:07,063 --> 00:02:08,775
- How you doing, brother?

29
00:02:08,775 --> 00:02:11,153
Hey, that was cute.

30
00:02:11,153 --> 00:02:12,405
- [Darcy] Yeah, I
thought you'd enjoy that.

31
00:02:12,405 --> 00:02:13,990
Now get in, man,
we're in a hurry.

32
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:23,253
- Lookin' good.

33
00:02:23,253 --> 00:02:26,758
(upbeat electronic music)

34
00:02:29,136 --> 00:02:32,308
(siren blaring)

35
00:02:32,308 --> 00:02:33,768
What's with the cherry?

36
00:02:33,768 --> 00:02:35,187
- Well, the Black Rose Boys
are up to some mischief.

37
00:02:35,187 --> 00:02:37,606
- Black Rose, huh?
- Russians.

38
00:02:37,606 --> 00:02:39,025
I thought you should
hit the ground running.

39
00:02:46,243 --> 00:02:49,122
(gunshots banging)

40
00:02:55,924 --> 00:02:58,886
So they tell me the crime rate
in the Big Apple has dropped.

41
00:02:58,886 --> 00:03:01,056
- Yeah, action's
getting a little stale.

42
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:03,016
I'm glad to be out of there.

43
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,980
- I can tell the boys here are
gonna love you coming back.

44
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:08,149
- I can always ride with
you, little brother.

45
00:03:08,149 --> 00:03:10,444
- Just remember, that's
ride with me, not on me.

46
00:03:24,964 --> 00:03:27,926
(gunshots banging)

47
00:03:35,562 --> 00:03:37,064
- Gimme a break.

48
00:03:37,064 --> 00:03:38,483
If it wasn't for me, you'd
probably be rotting away

49
00:03:38,483 --> 00:03:40,861
in some cell with a bunkmate
who calls you Sally.

50
00:03:41,821 --> 00:03:42,697
- I miss those lectures.

51
00:03:42,697 --> 00:03:43,532
That's beautiful.

52
00:03:44,742 --> 00:03:46,202
- You know, by the
way, those cigarettes,

53
00:03:46,202 --> 00:03:48,164
they kill more people
than car accidents, drugs,

54
00:03:48,164 --> 00:03:51,251
alcohol, and bullets combined.

55
00:03:51,251 --> 00:03:52,210
- You quit again, huh?

56
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,838
How long's it been?

57
00:03:53,838 --> 00:03:55,799
- Three days.
- Three days. (laughs)

58
00:03:56,967 --> 00:03:59,805
(gunshots banging)

59
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:11,071
(gunshots banging)

60
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,117
Let's go.

61
00:04:15,117 --> 00:04:16,745
- Put that away.

62
00:04:16,745 --> 00:04:18,706
- Oh, you've got that
look in your eye.

63
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:23,796
(gunshots banging)

64
00:04:34,061 --> 00:04:36,982
(gunshots banging)

65
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,455
(tires screeching)

66
00:04:47,455 --> 00:04:48,289
- What the?

67
00:04:48,289 --> 00:04:51,210
(fence clattering)

68
00:04:52,419 --> 00:04:55,341
(gunshots banging)

69
00:04:57,301 --> 00:05:00,180
(gunshots banging)

70
00:05:04,687 --> 00:05:05,855
- We can't stay here.

71
00:05:05,855 --> 00:05:06,815
- What are you doing?

72
00:05:06,815 --> 00:05:08,985
- Let's go inside, inside.

73
00:05:10,904 --> 00:05:12,657
Split up.
- Of course.

74
00:05:19,625 --> 00:05:23,380
- Cowboy Ray Harlan, I
should've known it was you.

75
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:24,214
- How you doin', Frenchy?

76
00:05:24,214 --> 00:05:25,174
Good to see you.

77
00:05:25,174 --> 00:05:26,384
- What's going on in there, huh?

78
00:05:26,384 --> 00:05:27,218
- They knocked off a
high-stake poker game.

79
00:05:27,218 --> 00:05:27,928
- Frenchy, the door.

80
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:30,432
Clear!

81
00:06:05,772 --> 00:06:07,942
Just like hold times, eh?

82
00:06:07,942 --> 00:06:12,949
- And as usual I'm
still watching your
back, little brother.

83
00:06:19,667 --> 00:06:21,002
Nice homecoming.

84
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:18,541
(gunshots banging)

85
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:28,305
Go.

86
00:07:28,305 --> 00:07:31,226
(gunshots banging)

87
00:07:41,991 --> 00:07:44,911
(gunshots banging)

88
00:07:49,292 --> 00:07:52,213
(gunshots banging)

89
00:07:59,515 --> 00:08:02,519
(man shouting)

90
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:04,522
- He's gone over,
the son of a fell.

91
00:08:07,943 --> 00:08:10,572
(man groaning)

92
00:08:14,161 --> 00:08:17,081
(gunshots banging)

93
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:21,296
You have the right
to remain silent.

94
00:08:21,296 --> 00:08:23,048
- Help, oh god!
(gunshots banging)

95
00:08:23,048 --> 00:08:24,258
- The guy's a real
Einstein, huh?

96
00:08:24,258 --> 00:08:25,134
- Noo too bright.

97
00:08:26,135 --> 00:08:27,470
- Help, help me!

98
00:08:28,889 --> 00:08:31,560
- I suggest you drop
that pea-shooter first.

99
00:08:32,895 --> 00:08:34,689
- Help, help!

100
00:08:34,689 --> 00:08:35,857
- Drop it!

101
00:08:35,857 --> 00:08:37,526
- Okay, okay, okay.

102
00:08:43,242 --> 00:08:45,120
Okay, it is gone, okay.

103
00:08:50,044 --> 00:08:52,255
Help me, help me.

104
00:08:52,255 --> 00:08:53,173
- How you doin'?

105
00:08:53,173 --> 00:08:54,217
- [Man] Help.

106
00:08:54,217 --> 00:08:55,552
- Say uncle.

107
00:08:55,552 --> 00:08:57,179
- You crazy bastard, uncle.

108
00:08:58,639 --> 00:09:00,058
- Say uncle please.

109
00:09:01,893 --> 00:09:04,189
- Uncle, uncle please, help me.

110
00:09:08,111 --> 00:09:11,115
- I don't know, I say
heads we drop him.

111
00:09:11,115 --> 00:09:12,117
- Heads we drop him.

112
00:09:13,619 --> 00:09:15,329
- I don't have any change,
you have any change?

113
00:09:15,329 --> 00:09:16,956
- What are you doing?

114
00:09:16,956 --> 00:09:17,791
Oh my god.

115
00:09:19,042 --> 00:09:21,755
(dramatic music)

116
00:09:40,572 --> 00:09:42,075
- [Dispatcher] 911.

117
00:09:42,075 --> 00:09:44,578
- I think there's an
intruder in my apartment.

118
00:09:44,578 --> 00:09:46,998
- [Dispatcher] One moment.

119
00:09:46,998 --> 00:09:49,544
Megan Stewart, 2 Bolton
Street, Apartment 3.

120
00:09:49,544 --> 00:09:51,046
Mam, the police have
been dispatched.

121
00:09:51,046 --> 00:09:52,965
Stay where you are until
the officers arrive

122
00:09:52,965 --> 00:09:54,133
and keep the line open.

123
00:10:04,147 --> 00:10:05,983
- Hey, Frenchy, catch.

124
00:10:09,613 --> 00:10:10,699
Heads or tails?

125
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:12,868
- Tails!

126
00:10:15,538 --> 00:10:20,337
Hey, listen, Yankee and
Doodle, dispatch got a call.

127
00:10:20,337 --> 00:10:21,464
Intruder.
- What are you doing?

128
00:10:21,464 --> 00:10:23,424
- 2 Bolton, number 3.

129
00:10:23,424 --> 00:10:25,636
The building behind you.

130
00:10:25,636 --> 00:10:26,804
- What'd he say?

131
00:10:26,804 --> 00:10:27,722
- Come on, move!
- Where are you going?

132
00:10:27,722 --> 00:10:28,807
- Get this guy down, now!

133
00:10:29,683 --> 00:10:30,685
Let's move!

134
00:10:30,685 --> 00:10:33,188
- Hey, what are you doing?

135
00:10:33,188 --> 00:10:34,857
Freaks! You can't...

136
00:10:38,195 --> 00:10:40,907
(dramatic music)

137
00:10:45,122 --> 00:10:46,289
- You want the front or rear?

138
00:10:46,289 --> 00:10:47,500
- I'm a backdoor man.

139
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,168
Stay behind him, let's go.

140
00:11:23,258 --> 00:11:25,929
(Megan screams)

141
00:11:54,802 --> 00:11:57,764
- [Dispatcher] Miss Stewart,
are you still there?

142
00:11:57,764 --> 00:12:00,227
(Megan gasps)

143
00:12:09,990 --> 00:12:11,075
- Drop the weapon.

144
00:12:12,244 --> 00:12:15,581
- Do not test me,
I will kill her.

145
00:12:15,581 --> 00:12:17,000
- You kill her, I kill you.

146
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,585
- Hey!
- Shut up!

147
00:12:18,585 --> 00:12:19,879
- Drop the weapon
and maybe your lawyer

148
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:21,172
will have you out on
the street by morning.

149
00:12:21,172 --> 00:12:22,674
Now drop it.

150
00:12:22,674 --> 00:12:27,681
- Yeah, don't do this, don't.

151
00:12:30,477 --> 00:12:31,479
- All right.

152
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:34,775
- Easy.

153
00:12:49,295 --> 00:12:50,380
(gunshots banging)

154
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:53,009
(Ivan groaning)

155
00:12:57,014 --> 00:13:01,228
- What kind of stupid, macho,
Neanderthal move was that?

156
00:13:01,228 --> 00:13:02,480
- You're welcome.

157
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,400
- Who the hell do
you think you are?

158
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,526
You could've killed me.

159
00:13:06,570 --> 00:13:08,613
- Ain't life a bowl of cherries.

160
00:13:08,613 --> 00:13:10,491
(Frenchy and Darcy laughing)

161
00:13:10,491 --> 00:13:11,910
- Ouch.

162
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:15,039
- I work for the police
department, I've got friends.

163
00:13:15,039 --> 00:13:17,543
I want your badge number
because I'm gonna report you!

164
00:13:19,253 --> 00:13:21,215
- What the hell happened here?

165
00:13:21,215 --> 00:13:23,426
- That moron blew up my toilet.

166
00:13:24,928 --> 00:13:26,639
- Well, that's a hell
of a first day, brother,

167
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:28,600
considering you
haven't punched in yet.

168
00:13:31,104 --> 00:13:33,398
- [Ivan] Be careful!

169
00:13:33,398 --> 00:13:35,485
- Wait till you
get to your cell.

170
00:13:35,485 --> 00:13:36,612
Cuff him.

171
00:13:36,612 --> 00:13:39,281
- [Darcy] Come on, scumbag.

172
00:13:39,281 --> 00:13:41,702
- We got right to
make phone call.

173
00:13:41,702 --> 00:13:44,122
- Don't tell me about
your rights, you moron.

174
00:13:44,122 --> 00:13:46,751
- Can I have some
service over here?

175
00:13:46,751 --> 00:13:47,585
Go on.

176
00:13:49,755 --> 00:13:50,756
Gonna miss you guys.

177
00:14:01,437 --> 00:14:02,273
Go in.

178
00:14:09,282 --> 00:14:10,116
- Lou.

179
00:14:12,036 --> 00:14:15,081
- Goddamn, it's good to see you!

180
00:14:18,211 --> 00:14:20,924
It's hard to believe you've
only been here a few hours.

181
00:14:20,924 --> 00:14:22,634
The whole station is buzzing.

182
00:14:23,803 --> 00:14:26,222
Your reputation as a
hard-ass precedes you.

183
00:14:28,225 --> 00:14:30,353
(upbeat rock music)

184
00:14:30,353 --> 00:14:33,316
- [Vlad] The reports
I am getting are not
favorable, Mikael.

185
00:14:33,316 --> 00:14:34,400
- [Mikael] Yes, Uncle.

186
00:14:35,527 --> 00:14:38,239
- [Vlad] You waste
my time and my money.

187
00:14:38,239 --> 00:14:39,783
- Uncle, they are lies.

188
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:44,414
We've had a few setbacks,
but nothing unusual.

189
00:14:44,414 --> 00:14:49,338
I need more money for
bribery, to compete.

190
00:14:49,338 --> 00:14:51,800
In this respect, the
competition is well ahead of us.

191
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,887
- [Vlad] No, there will
be no more investment

192
00:14:54,887 --> 00:14:56,598
until I see results.

193
00:14:56,598 --> 00:15:00,103
This opportunity you
are squandering will
not last forever.

194
00:15:00,103 --> 00:15:01,689
And Mikael.

195
00:15:01,689 --> 00:15:03,358
- Yes, Uncle Vladimir?

196
00:15:03,358 --> 00:15:05,527
- [Vlad] I have just
learned that my old friend

197
00:15:05,527 --> 00:15:08,615
Lieutenant Ray Harlan has
arrived in your back yard.

198
00:15:08,615 --> 00:15:10,284
- [Mikael] Should
this concern me?

199
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,786
- [Vlad] Very much so.

200
00:15:11,786 --> 00:15:13,873
He has been a big problem
for me here in New York.

201
00:15:13,873 --> 00:15:17,210
Do not underestimate him, he
doesn't play by the rules.

202
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:18,254
- Neither do we.

203
00:15:19,506 --> 00:15:21,383
Do not worry, I will
take care of it.

204
00:15:22,635 --> 00:15:24,428
- [Vlad] Do not let
me down, Mikael.

205
00:15:24,428 --> 00:15:27,475
Even if you are my
blood, you will die.

206
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:46,209
- Now, Ray, you know
better than most

207
00:15:46,209 --> 00:15:47,711
how Russians love payola.

208
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:51,884
You talk to me, huh, and
anyone I say is okay.

209
00:15:53,719 --> 00:15:55,806
We'll put you on the
clock starting tomorrow.

210
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,435
Okay then.

211
00:16:00,896 --> 00:16:02,482
Darcy, get him out of here.

212
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:11,829
Oh, hey, tonight you and
Darceú are coming for dinner.

213
00:16:13,706 --> 00:16:15,249
- Oh, oh.

214
00:16:20,549 --> 00:16:21,383
- What?

215
00:16:22,552 --> 00:16:24,972
What are you looking
so warm and fuzzy for?

216
00:16:24,972 --> 00:16:27,016
- Thanks for bringing me back.

217
00:16:27,016 --> 00:16:31,064
New York was getting a little
shaky, you know, empty.

218
00:16:34,276 --> 00:16:36,696
You two guys are the only
family I got, you know.

219
00:16:38,157 --> 00:16:39,450
It's good to be home, Lou.

220
00:16:42,497 --> 00:16:43,539
- Go, will ya?

221
00:16:43,539 --> 00:16:44,625
I'm about to shed a tear.

222
00:16:46,543 --> 00:16:47,378
- Thanks.

223
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:57,726
(light jazzy music)

224
00:17:05,862 --> 00:17:07,573
- It's great having
you boys here.

225
00:17:08,866 --> 00:17:11,620
I miss all the great
dinners we used to have.

226
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:14,541
- Great, I don't
know about that.

227
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:17,837
- Hey, wise guy, I
make a great stew.

228
00:17:17,837 --> 00:17:20,841
- Brace yourself, Ray,
here comes the stew speech.

229
00:17:20,841 --> 00:17:22,886
- Stew's a real healthy meal.

230
00:17:22,886 --> 00:17:26,099
Did you know that poor people
don't get sick like the rich

231
00:17:26,099 --> 00:17:28,477
because they eat a lot of stews?

232
00:17:28,477 --> 00:17:29,729
Yeah, it's cheap to make,

233
00:17:29,729 --> 00:17:32,692
and it has all the
necessary vitamins.

234
00:17:32,692 --> 00:17:35,195
Now eat, you
ungrateful delinquents.

235
00:17:35,195 --> 00:17:36,738
(Ray and Darcy laughing)

236
00:17:36,738 --> 00:17:38,366
- I'm sorry, Lou, it must
have been tough for you, huh?

237
00:17:38,366 --> 00:17:40,369
Raising a couple of
tough heads like us.

238
00:17:41,996 --> 00:17:43,122
- Ah, it wasn't so bad.

239
00:17:44,834 --> 00:17:47,796
As a matter of fact, most of
the time we had a ball, right?

240
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:52,302
You boys, you turned
out just fine.

241
00:17:55,599 --> 00:17:57,017
I love you both very much.

242
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:03,276
Welcome home, Ray.

243
00:18:06,572 --> 00:18:07,406
- Thanks.

244
00:18:13,249 --> 00:18:14,834
- [Crowd] Surprise!

245
00:18:19,298 --> 00:18:23,304
- Hey, Frenchy.
- Hey, nice to see you, buddy.

246
00:18:23,304 --> 00:18:24,180
Hey, that's great.

247
00:18:26,851 --> 00:18:27,685
What's up?

248
00:18:30,063 --> 00:18:31,274
- Tequila.

249
00:18:31,274 --> 00:18:33,067
♪ You got to reap
just what you sow ♪

250
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,194
- Hey, Darcy.

251
00:18:35,070 --> 00:18:36,364
- Welcome home, Ray.

252
00:18:36,364 --> 00:18:38,825
♪ It's the same the
whole world over ♪

253
00:18:38,825 --> 00:18:40,787
- Welcome home, mon ami.

254
00:18:40,787 --> 00:18:42,289
- Thanks, Frenchy.

255
00:18:42,289 --> 00:18:44,042
- Hey, Ray, this is
my new partner, Blue.

256
00:18:44,042 --> 00:18:45,251
- Hey, Blue.

257
00:18:45,251 --> 00:18:46,921
- Hey, Ray, heard a lot
of things about you.

258
00:18:46,921 --> 00:18:48,798
- Nothing good, I hope.

259
00:18:48,798 --> 00:18:50,884
- As good as good gets.
